title: For Sale/Trade:  Gun safe - Heritage 12 locking bolts - built like a tank. TRADE?
postcontent:
This is a Heritage gun safe - I replaced the combination style dial lock with a brand new S&G (high end) digital keypad combination lock. You can set it to any combination you want...quick access for you - impossible for everyone else.

The safe has internal hinges as well... no way to pry the door off.

This safe has 5 bolts on each side, one on the top, and one on the bottom for a total of 12 and they all move in and out when you turn the wheel... they all lock into place when the door is closed and safe is locked.

There are slots on the left for 8 rifles or shotguns. The right side is all shelved. You could modify this to hold twice as many long guns if you wanted and still have some shelf space.

The interior is a tan suede. And I don't see a fire rating on it - but that sticker may have been removed... I can't find a model number so I can't be sure of a fire rating. However a thief would have to camp out to try and get in this thing. The door and the body of this thing is made out of rediculously thick steel.

Now although it functions perfectly... it's not perfect. It has been moved around and has a few scuffs and chips in the paint- you can see some of these in the pics.

If you trade me for this safe - you will come and get it :) Bring a few buddies and we'll unbolt it from the concrete and get it into a truck. I do not have a truck - so you're on your own there.

What I'm looking for in trade is (and feel free to offer ANYTHING at all ... worst I can say is no - I like all sorts of pistols and rifles ... nice 22's, carry guns, full size pistols, whatever ) :

1911 - Flawless Springfield loaded with all accessories / box - or a higher end model than that. Basically a top notch factory 1911... not really looking for a custom built gun - but let me know what you have.

Other than that... let me know what you have. I don't think you could get close to a safe like this one for under a grand.

I'm open to combinations of rifles / pistols / whatever. I might like to have a Remington SPS in .223 with some quality glass on it - or maybe the SPS and a pistol? How about a nice hunting rifle in .308 with quality glass and something else?

Just let me know what you have - I'll take the best or most interesting offer :) The safe isn't going anywhere... the incredible hulk couldn't carry this thing off.

Oh and sorry for the crappy pics... it's bolted down in a pretty tight spot. I couldn't get back and get better ones and it's dark in there. There is another shelf up top you can't see from the pics.
